Hey there, we could probably deprecate bag of words and use this one with unigrams
Also please keep the space separator for backward compatibility

> > feature = feature + ":" + text[i + y];
> > feature = feature + " " + text[i + y];

@danielruss this is good to merge, code changes are all good and I did also run a couple of tests to ensure it doesn't break anything. After you resolved smarthi comment from above we can get it finally in.

We will need to squash all your commits, you can do that by yourself if you want and you probably need to rebase to see the checkstyle work we did.

Please also notice we switched from trunk to master branch.

I don't think there's a checkstyle to enforce Java 8 conventions, but the
IDE should be able to flag this if u set the default language level to Java
8 with Lambdas.

